description: In one of the most beautiful canal houses of Amsterdam, the Cromhout House, you will meet a number of notable collectors. Over the years they have donated their diverse collections to the city of Amsterdam. The Cromhouthuis is the house of collectors. Wandering through the different rooms, an audio tour tells you the story of influential collectors such as Dreesmann, Backer and Lopez Suasso. The Cromhout family, who lived here for almost two centuries, formed the core of what we now consider World Heritage: the canal belt! They were also prominent art collectors. In de buurt van Volendam gaan we zelfs ook bij een kaasmakerij binnen kijken, waar de kaasmeester uit zal leggen hoe Goudse en Edammer kazen gemaakt worden. En we bezoeken een klompenmakerij de geheimen prijs zal geven van de Dutch wooden shoes die over de hele wereld bekend zijn!De volgende halte zal in Marken zijn, waar het lijkt of sinds de 17e eeuw de tijd stil heeft gestaan. We bekijken de gezellige vissershuisjes, de haven en de protestantse kerk.Aan het einde van de dagtrip ontvang je van je gids alle informatie die je nodig hebt voor je rondvaart door de Amsterdamse grachten. The museum provides a view of the 'landscape' taking shape in photography; it presents photographers, artists and forms of photography which do justice to visual quality and which can be counted among the medium's major, but also lesser known, highlights. title: MLB Gallery
description: Welcome to the MLB Gallery: an artist's exhibition space on the Witte de Withstraat in Amsterdam' trendy old west. Each month we feature a new exhibition. And they are often a surprise. The range of styles and techniques is from gifted amateurs to professional artists with credentials. The resulting artworks are always different if not unique. Sometimes beautiful, sometimes touching, sometimes experimental. But, again, more of than not, surprising! It's affordable art because MLB does NOT take a big commission on sold artwork. The artist is the director, promoter and sales person who is present during the opening hours of the space. Background Some ten years ago, Marie-Louise Boel found a former vegetable shop for rent. She needed only an office space and, as for the rest of the area, something that would be attractive to her clients. A gallery seemed to be the perfect solution. And, now, a decade later, it is a focal point on the Witte de Withstraat. The aim is to show "art" in all its manifestations. The artist rents the gallery space. Ms Boel, along with Mieke Schulte, the assistant gallery holder, advise the artist on the rudimentaries of mounting an exhibition. Your own solo show The duration for a show is one month. You rent the space for this period. You design and make the posters, invitation cards and arrange for the opening reception with our help and professional support. Over the course of the exhibition you sit, at the gallery, during the opening hours for the space. The minimal time you are expected to be present is on Saturdays between noon and six p.m. Duo shows, featuring a painter and sculpture, as an example, is possible. The gallery is also open on Fridays between noon and six p.m.

title: Museum De Dageraad
description: Behind the wave-shaped facade of the famous working-class housing complex De Dageraad, you will find information about the art and architecture of the Amsterdam School. At the beginning of the last century, H.P. Berlage designed the now famous Plan Zuid. He introduced a new way of urban planning, in which there was room for wide streets, atmospheric squares and green parks. The characteristic architecture of the many Amsterdam School artists still adorns the street plan. The expressionistic facades and beautiful ornaments are recognizable throughout the neighborhood. Residential complex De Dageraad is the Amsterdam School in its purest form. Architects Michel de Klerk and Piet Kramer were commissioned to design all facets of the streetscape. In addition to the street facades, they also designed the rear facades and floor plans. This led to a form of total art in which beauty was central. Museum De Dageraad is the starting point for many walks and cycling tours in the neighbourhood.

title: Royal Palace Amsterdam
description: The Royal Palace Amsterdam is in use by the Dutch Royal House. Most of the year, the Royal Palace is alsof open for visitors. You are welcome to discover the rich history and interior of this magnificent building in the heart of Amsterdam. Visitors are welcome to discover the building's rich past and legacies left by it's successive occupants - as Amsterdam's Town Hall for 150 years, the French Royal and Imperial Palace for 5 years and the Palace of the House of Orange for the past two centuries. The Royal Palace was built in the seventeenth century as the Town Hall of Amsterdam, after a design by Jacob van Campen. It's paintings and sculptures were made by some of the most distinguished artists of the time and allude to the city's influence and prosperity in the Dutch Golden Age. In 1808 Louis Napoleon, brother of the French Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte, became King of Holland and converted the Town Hall into a Palace. The superb collection of Empire furniture, clocks and chandeliers date from that period. The collection of Empire furniture is one of the best preserved and most complete collections in the world. The rooms in the Palace are decorated with artworks from the collection of the House of Orange-Nassau Historic Collections Trust. Many paintings show the various members of the family of Orange-Nassau

Voor degenen die het museum zelf niet kunnen bezoeken biedt het Van Gogh Museum de collectie en een virtuele reis door het leven van Van Gogh aan op de officiële website, Facebook en Instagram.

title: Yab Yum Unlocked
description: VISITING YAB YUM POSSIBLE AGAIN! The world famous and former brothel Yab Yum opens its doors to a wider audience. The well-known 17th-century building with the green lantern on the 'Singel' in Amsterdam has been transformed into a fascinating concept: YAB YUM Unlocked. Recently, the genuine YAB YUM feeling is brought back to life. YAB YUM Unlocked is a wonderful exhibition and a 'Real Life Club Experience' at the same time. YAB YUM Unlocked takes you back to the years during which YAB YUM was famous all over the world. How it all came about, who visited and why was the club so popular? You'll visit the luxurious bar and famous 'caviar room', you'll see how founder Theo Heuft ever got the idea and how the club became one of the biggest status symbols for straight arrows and hoodlums alike. It also takes you behind the scenes of this well-organized company, a booming enterprise with an annual turnover of millions.
